The accident airplane was a Tecnam P92, a high-wing, single-engine, light sport airplane, with 
fixed landing gear. It was powered by a 100-horsepower, 4-cylinder, reciprocating Rotax 912 
engine, and a fixed pitch propeller. The airplane's airworthiness certificate is in the Special, 
Light Sport (S-LSA) category. The fuselage was a semi-monocoque construction with a mixture 
of thin aluminum covered tube structure. A review of the airplane's maintenance records 
revealed that the last condition inspection was completed October 22, 2015, at an airplane and 
engine total time of 2,385.57 hours.
