The Houston Southwest Airport (AXH) is a public-use, non-towered airport, located 15 miles 
southwest of Houston, Texas. Pilots use ommon raffic dvisory requency (CTAF) for 
communications. The airport has a single asphalt runway; runway 9/27, measuring 5,002 ft. 
long by 100 ft. wide. The airport is at an elevation of 68.9 ft mean sea level and has an AWOS 
station located on the field.
